    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Historical devices of varied design, but usually with a handheld tray intended to hold magnesium flash powder that would be ignited at the moment of exposure of a photographic plate. These were used before the advent of flash bulbs and later electronic flash devices.</Note_Text>
